Scott S. Cowen  Trustee and President, Tulane UniversityAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 7 Board Members in 7 different organizations across 8 different industries.See Board Relationships70--
Background

		Dr. Scott S. Cowen has been the President of Tulane University in New Orleans since 1998. Dr. Cowen has been President of The Seymour S Goodman Memorial Professor of Business in Tulane's A.B., Freeman School of Business since July 1998. He has been Professor of Economics in the Faculty of Liberal Arts and Sciences since July 1998. From 1984 to July 1998, he served as Dean and Albert J. Weatherhead III Professor of Management, Weatherhead School of Management, Case Western ... Reserve University. Prior to his departure in 1998, he served at Case Western Reserve University in various capacities since 1976. He has an extensive experience in business as a Corporate Director and Consultant. He has been a Director at Forest City Realty Trust, Inc since 1989 and serves as its Lead Director. He has been an Independent Director of  Newell Brands Inc. since 1999 and of Rubbermaid Incorporated since 1997. Dr. Cowen has been a Director of Barnes & Noble, Inc. since April 2014. He serves as Trustee of University of Notre Dame. He serves as Director of Society Corporation, Weatherhead Industries, Inc. and Cyberex Corporation. He has been a Director of American Greetings Corp. since June 1, 2016. He serves as Trustee of Tulane University. He has been a Director of Society National Bank since 2014. He serves as a Director of Fabri-Centers of America Inc., and is on the Board of Advisors of Charles Fradin Inc., and Copley Industries. He served as a Director at Greater New Orleans Inc. He served as a Director of Jo-Ann Stores Inc. from 1987 to March 18, 2011 and its Lead Director from August 2007 to March 18, 2011. He served as a Director of LDI Corp. since 1989. He served as a Director of Premier Industrial Corp. since 1986. He served as an Independent Director of Nacco Industries Inc. since 2015 until August 10, 2016. He served as a Director of American Greetings Corp. from 1989 to October 2013. He has been Director of Newell Brands since April 18, 2016. He serves as Member of the Boards of American Council on Education and National Association of Independent Colleges and Universities (educational institutions). He sits on several community boards, including those of the New Orleans Business Council, New Orleans Regional Chamber of Commerce, United Way of Greater New Orleans and Committee for a Better New Orleans. He is the Co-Author of four books and has published more than 90 articles in academic and professional journals focused on issues dealing with corporate governance, strategic planning and the development of management systems. Dr. Cowen received his Bachelor's Degree from the University of Connecticut. He received his masters and doctoral degrees, respectively, from The George Washington University in the fields of finance and management.Read Full Background




